# Default: let git pick text vs. binary and normalize line endings.
* text=auto

# The DOS/Pascal legacy sources are CRLF in their original form. Treat
# them as binary so git never rewrites or normalizes their line endings
# — that "rewriting" was producing 25k+ spurious modifications in
# `git status` every time the working tree was touched from a system
# with a different `core.autocrlf` setting. After this file is
# committed, run `git add --renormalize legacy/` once to clear any
# existing CRLF/LF churn from the working tree.
legacy/** -text
